  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide uppercase mb-10">
        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How often should conveyor PM be performed?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Daily: visual inspection, tracking check, debris removal. Weekly: tension check, roller spin test, sensor test. Monthly: bearing lubrication, motor temperature. Quarterly: drive inspection, electrical connections. Annually: full inspection, motor insulation test, controls backup. Food-grade and high-speed lines need more frequent PM.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How do I track a conveyor belt?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Run the belt empty. If it drifts right, tighten the right-side tail pulley bolt by 1/4 turn. Wait 3-5 revolutions. Repeat with small adjustments until centered. Then load product and verify. If tracking does not respond, check for material buildup on pulleys, belt damage, splice failure, or frame misalignment.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What causes a conveyor belt to slip?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Five causes: insufficient belt tension (increase tension), wet or contaminated drive pulley (clean it), worn pulley lagging (replace it), overloaded belt (reduce load or increase motor), or seized roller creating drag (replace roller). Check each in order , tension is the most common cause.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            When should I replace a conveyor belt?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Replace when you see: edge fraying over 1/2 inch, surface cracks or delamination, visible carcass through the cover, belt stretch beyond tensioner range, splice failure, or hardening/brittleness. For <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">food belts</a>, also replace when the surface cannot be cleaned to sanitary standards. See <a href="/resources/conveyor-belting/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">belt types guide</a> for material-specific life ranges.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
